cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with error correcting codes in network coding, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of lattices and the metric based on the height function suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures (cs.DS). The application of the model to submodule lattices and the computation of sphere packing and covering bounds suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the use of codes and the presentation of bounds suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
